  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of this study is to compare the efficacy and safety of the combination therapy
      with enzalutamide + androgen deprivation therapy (ADT) and the combination therapy with
      flutamide + ADT in patients with castration resistant prostate cancer who have relapsed
      during combined androgen blockade (CAB) therapy with bicalutamide and ADT. This study will
      also investigate the order of alternative antiandrogen therapy (AAT) by changing the 1st line
      medication after relapse of prostate-specific antigen (PSA).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
